        "origin": "web-extension",
        "content": "<p> Shihāb al-Dīn<sup>  </sup>Yāqūt ibn ‘Abd-Allāh al-Rūmī al-Ḥamawī (d. 1229) was a famous Muslim geographer, known for his work <em>Mu‘jam al-Buldān </em>(The Lexicon of Countries), which is an immensely valuable encyclopedia of the Islamic world in his time. The <em>Mu‘jam</em> is as much a work of history, biography, and literature as it is a masterpiece of geography.    </p>",
